Diagnosis.
Female can be recognised by the distinct colour patterns on body (
Fig. 17–19
); both sexes with infuscated bands on femora (
Figs 17–19
) and a band on tibia IV, epigyne atrium small, teardrop-shaped to oval, closed anteriorly (
Fig. 55
). Male with broad RTA base (
Fig. 53
); resemble 

M. irmatrix


sp. n.

but copulatory organs and colour of body and legs different.
